                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13425390" author="enis" created="Mon, 30 Jul 2012 23:38:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doc from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6241&quot; title=&quot;HBaseCluster interface for interacting with the cluster from system tests &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, with added sections on running the tests in mini/distributed mode + chaos monkey. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13427411" author="apurtell" created="Thu, 2 Aug 2012 16:13:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doc update looks good Enis.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggest removing the rhetorical question in the &lt;tt&gt;maven.build.commanas.integration.tests2&lt;/tt&gt; section but that&apos;s my personal taste. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider providing a CLI example for how to run with the ChaosMonkey. Maybe show how to target it against the running test cluster? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13429416" author="stack" created="Mon, 6 Aug 2012 20:52:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good to me Enis.  What you think of Andrew&apos;s comments above?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13448755" author="mdrzal" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2012 14:01:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good, with the exception of the points that Andrew made.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13448878" author="stack" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2012 16:47:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Enis Want to have a go at addressing Andrew comments?  Or just paste a CLI example here and I&apos;ll take care of getting above committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13448933" author="enis" created="Wed, 5 Sep 2012 17:59:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry guys, I was waiting for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6241&quot; title=&quot;HBaseCluster interface for interacting with the cluster from system tests &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to be resolved first before updating the patch. Without &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-6241&quot; title=&quot;HBaseCluster interface for interacting with the cluster from system tests &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-6241&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-6241&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; finalized, if we commit the doc, it might be confusing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13459175" author="stack" created="Wed, 19 Sep 2012 22:41:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can remove the rhetorical question from the patch but do you have Andrew&apos;s suggested CLI ChaosMonkey example?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13459266" author="enis" created="Thu, 20 Sep 2012 01:01:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll update the patch tomorrow with Andrew&apos;s suggestions. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472975" author="stack" created="Wed, 10 Oct 2012 04:00:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any luck w/ this one Enis?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13481749" author="enis" created="Mon, 22 Oct 2012 20:23:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry I could not get to this sooner. Other than the CLI commands for ChaosMonkey, is there anything else missing or improved upon. I can update the patch with suggestions. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13485561" author="stack" created="Sun, 28 Oct 2012 03:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you supply the chaosmonkey example, I&apos;ll take care of the rest. Thanks Enis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13500800" author="enis" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 02:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed the irrelevant question, and added significantly more documentation about ClusterManager/HBaseClusterManager and ChaosMonkey together with cmd-line example and log output. Should be good to go. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13506257" author="stack" created="Thu, 29 Nov 2012 06:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the excellent doc Enis.  Let me commit...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13506263" author="stack" created="Thu, 29 Nov 2012 06:44:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minor diff from v2 to make the patch go in...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13506265" author="stack" created="Thu, 29 Nov 2012 06:45:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.  Nice doc. Enis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13508991" author="enis" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 19:56:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving the issue. Stack, I could not find info about how do we update the site. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509065" author="stack" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 21:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#hbase.org&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://hbase.apache.org/book.html#hbase.org&lt;/a&gt;  Let me know if doesn&apos;t make sense.  I just pushed out doc so your fancy integration test stuff should show on the site soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13509069" author="enis" created="Mon, 3 Dec 2012 21:33:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Cool. Thanks Stack. I had checked the book, but somehow I missed it apparently. My b. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13775274" author="stack" created="Mon, 23 Sep 2013 18:31:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
